This is not the first time MCSK is in the limelight for the wrong reasons.Last year, the organisation came under attack from Kenyan artistes and their fans over royalties. Music Copyright Society of Kenya (MCSK), umbrella body which pays musicians their royalties, has suffered a blow after its license was revoked by the Kenya Copyright Board (KCB).
The Board revoked the operating licence of MCSK after it failed to adhere to existing licensing conditions, including failing to submit a complete authenticated list of members.



