Some of the popular musicians who accused MCSK of exploiting them are Khaligraph Jones and King Kaka. They castigated MCSK, terming the organisation as unprofessional for failing to honour its obligations to musicians.
However, the official confirmed that the licences of other MCSK partners, the Kenya Association of Music Producers (KAMP) and Performers Rights Society of Kenya (PRISK), were not canceled and remain valid.
Transparency purpose
The Board also expressed satisfaction with the progress made on the National Rights Registry and the Collective Management Organisations (CMO) ICT system noting it was substantially complete and already serving its intended registration of copyright and transparency purpose.



