“Though there is little more work that remains to perfect the system, over 7,500 new works and over Sh20 million have been collected over the system by (CMO) since June 2020,” Mr Mathiu disclosed.
The Board also approved a policy that will guide the operations of the CMOs to ensure good corporate practices among them transparency, cost saving and fitness for purpose in service of its members. 
“The approved policy will be uploaded on the KECOBO website for final public comments before implementation as from 16th December to 15th January 2021,” added Mr Mathiu.
KECOBO Executive Director, Mr Edward Sigei, said the CMOs Royalty Collection system offers those that exploit music in the course of business an opportunity to obtain a consolidated music licence from the comfort of their homes. 
